{"/service/ndnp/cohi/batch_cohi_alta_ver01/data/sn86002159/00513680430/1921011401/1000.xml":{"full_text":"r.-mmlngu.&w-\u2018.m-&Q.\nYour Interests and Ours\nIt is as much to our advantage for you to buy P!\nyour goods at a reasonable price as it is to your p\nadvantage. We want you to come again. I our\ncustomers came to buy but once, we would soon p\nclose our doors.\nThat has always been the basis of our policy in p\n\u00e9\nrunning a mercantile business. We shall continue\nto keep that policy in our minds and in each and p\nevery transaction we have will endeavor to put\nourselves in the position of the customer who is p\n3\ncoming in the door. b\n8 P\nBuy at the store that has helped you along b\ng sTet i\nthese many years. We are all living in the same\ncommunity and have at heart the interset of this bf\n\nTown and country. Let's help each other when- '9\nP P\never we can do so.\nThere is no Mail Order House in the East or y\n4 P\nelsewhere that cares a rap about the condition of\nour roads nor what kind of schools we have,\nnor whether we have any churches, nor the other\n\ninterests thatare of help and value to the people\nhere b\nThe mercantile houses of this County are pay-\ning a large percentage of the taxes. If you appre- p i\nciate that, why not trade with one of them and keep\nyour money in your home community. P 1\nb\nThe Harris Bros. Merc. Co. b\nDOLORES, COLORADO j I\nbv AR Og W WSOV O W WO WWO U W\n:vvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvv\u2019vvva\n\n2 Success to You in 1921 w\n4 we feel grateful to our patrons for contributing to our suc-\nj cess throughout the year 1920, and we thank them for their\n4\n5 patronage. 4\nFor the year 1921, and future years, we wish them the\ngreatest measure of success and happiness, as we do all of our\npeople.\nP\n5 VINCENT E. ST. CLAIRE\nDOLORES, COLORADO\nol O o ol B B 088 B B B e B O 00 %o M O 3 BB B\n;vvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvwwvvv\u2018\n\ng Bl O R SELAL 3\nIf you want to sell, we can find a buyer. There is always\nsome one who wants it and who has the money to pay for it.\np\nP Place it in our hands for quick and advantageous sale.\nb If you want to buy, we can casily find a seller. There is\nalways some one who wants to make a change for some reason\norother. We haye every facility for locating it for you.\nWe can find a buyer or a seller while you are still thinking 4\nabout it. It 1s our business to know where to go and who to\nP see. Talk to us for quick action.\nDOLORES LOCATING AGENCY\nDOLORES, COLORADO\ns B B B B B B B B B M B OB B B B BB B BB B B B\n:tfi.*i\u2019hi\u00e9tfii***i\u2018b*'h**oo*****\u2019*tt-\ufb01&*\u2019**'\ufb01'\ufb01'\ufb01i'\ufb01*\ufb01\ufb01***.\n\n\ne\ni Cleaning and Pressing\n\n3 Give your clothes the best of care, and they\u2019ll\n*y y\n3 give you the best of wear.\n\n2 I thank you for your business of the past year s\n-E and wish you a prosperous new vyear. i l\no One block north of The Star office.\n\n\nLOURILLA WILSON\nPhone 365 DOLORES, COLORADO\n\n525 B o oeRoBERB R B R R R E R RGP ER TS SE l\ni L d\nMagazines and Periodicals\nBuy your favorite magazine at our newsstand.\n5 We take subscriptions to all magazines and period-\nicals at publishers\u2019 prices delivered to you by mail.\nCall for our 1921 subscription price catalogue.\nY p\nAGENTS FOR DENVER POST\ng CHAS. H. RASH CO.\nDOLORES, -7 &7- COLORADO o\nE\u2018.&\u201c\u201c\u2018l\ufb02&&x\ufb02n\ufb02l&x\ufb01\ufb01\u2018!&&\ufb01\u2018-&\u201c\ufb01\u2018J'\net ettt et ettt e\nIt must be hard to have such a large E\nincome that one can\u2019t pay the income\ntax on it,\nThe South has determined to reduce\nita cotton acreage to on\u00e9-half that ut\"l\nlast year. We\u2019ll just have to continue\nto wear silk socks, that\u2019s all.\nFor Sale or Trade.\nAlfalfa land Water right unexcelled.\nWhat have you to offer? J. Taylor, Jr.\nFlorence, Colorado.\n[4O-44\n\nBox Stationery at The Star office.\nCHARLES BEAR, PUBLISHER.\nEutered at the postofiice in Dolores, Colorado\nfor tranemission through the mails, as second\nclass mail matter,\nFriday, January 14, 1g21 1\nSUBSCHIPTION RATES i\nOue Yeour 3 R\nSix Months 1%\nThree Mouthe o ene eests ses 65\nCesh Must Accompsny Sobecription\nADVERTISING RATES\n1% ceuts, per slogle colume inch, per mouth\nlusertiobs of oue week, vtly, 25 ceuts per luch.\nLocals 10 ceuts per line each isaue\nDisplay ads. changed every two weeks without\nextra charge; weekly cisuges 3 cents per inch\nsdditional\nCopy tor chiange of sde should bLe supplied\njuot later than TUESDAY weon o iusure\nuppearance.\nMISCELLANEOUS,\nCardof thauks 75 ceuts resclutions of coudo\nletice 10 centa per Jine. siz words to the live.\nI B N et\nR1I0 GRANDE SOUTHERN R RI\nTIME CARD.\nARRIVE\nNo. 5~ Passenger from Telluride aud\nintermediate points...... 12 pmw\nNo. e\u2014-Punu\u2018:,r from Durango and l\nintermediate pointe e 28 P\nDEPART\nNo. 5\u2014Passenger for Durango aud in-\ntormediato pointa 12:45pm\nNo O\u2014Pnu.n\u2018for tor Telluride and In\ntermedinte points 1:l0pmw\n1 C. W. Lirry. Ageut,\nProsperity Ahead\nThere is much comfort to be|\n\u2018had from the statement rccentlyl\n{of Judge Elbert H. Gary, head of\n[the United States Steel corporation,\n[the greatest business concern the\niworld bhas ever produced. Judge|\nGary says a long period of wonder\n!ful prosperity is just ahead of the\nlpeople of the United States.\nWhen Judge Gary opens his\n\u00a5mouth he is in the habit of saying\nisomething, and he never says a\nithiug unless he knows what he\niIS talking about. He has been\na wise prophet in the past, because\nhe possesses the ability to read\nconditions and possibilities as they\nare.\nThere is no reason why his\nprophesy should not be ore of\nwisdom in this case, because there\n|is no reason why we should not\nprosper and every reason why we\nshould. Banks and financiers\ngenerally state that we have passed\nthrough our worst period of de\npression aud are now on the up\ngrade. Only the rankest kind of\npessimism can hold us back. And\u2018\nwho wants to be a pessimist when\n}evcr human instinct spurs us on to\noptimism?\nl Let's demonstrate our faith in\n|the return of prosperity by recog\n\u2018nizing the fact that it is here and\n|by doing our share toward its\nf!mainteuancc in this community.\nLet the watchword be production,\nwisdom in spending, and the em\n]ployment of a systematic course of\nsaving.\nt A proportionate amount of the\nprosperity of the country belongs\nto the people of this community.\nLet\u2019s get all we can and keep all}\nwe get. Other communities will\nbe doing the same.\nHere and There.\nl Young man, if you have a good\njob in the country, hang onto it.\nIf you want to walk the streets\nweek after week in a fruitless\nsearch for work, goto one of the\nbig cities.\nNewspapers are not parading the\nfact, but those who understand\nconditions in the large cities can\ntell you that employers are laying\noff theit help in increasing numbers\nevery day, and the end is nowhere\nin sight.\nA good country job has many;\nattractions The army of the un-\u2018\nployed has none.\nNOTICE\nThe undersigned, having begun the\nforeclosure of Chattel Mortgage upon\n\u2019lhe cattle described in Chattel Mort\n\u2018gage given the undersigned by David\nL. McCluer, recorded Book 64, page\n152, recordsin the Recorder\u2019s office of\nMontezuma County, Colorado, as\nbranded with the following brands.\nTwo slashes and cross on left side and\nhip; two slashes on right side and one\ncross on hip; and one slash and two\ncrosses on left shoulder, side and hip;\na suitable reward is hereby offered for\ninformation that will secure the loca\ntion of any of said cattle so that the\nsame may be obtained by said mort\nragee. ol\nJ. J. HARRIS COMPANY, Bankers.\nDated January, 11, 1921,\nFirst Pub. January 14, 1921.\nLast Pub. January 21, 1921.\nSubscribefor The Dolores Star.\nSECHRIST PRESSURE COOKER\nThe reasons why people buy the Sechrist Pres\nsure Cooker are:\n1. It saves at least half on fuel bill.\n2. It saves two-thirds cooking time.\n3. It cooks cheap cuts of meat or old chicken\ntender.\n4. Tt will serve as an ideal canner when canning\nseason comes around.\n5. It is made of rolled plate aluminum that is\neasily cleaned, has a beautiful finish,\nstraight sides, no rubber gasket, and has\nan accurate safety valve.\nT. H. AKIN MERCANTILE CO\nDOLORES, COLORADO\nHealthy Increase of Freight Business at the R. G. S. Depot\nThe following table shows the car-load-lot business done through the\nlocal depot the past three years. You will notice that there has been an\nincrease in all lines except two. The reason for the decrease in the number\nof sheep handled last year was that the road was out and the sheep had to\nbe driven to the summer range instead of shipped as in former years:\nR R TR T T e i i\nsleleldlg 2]\n|S |8 |m |<|B\"| &3 |g7\n1918 et e|e i\nJanuary. 11 2 2\nFebruary. 4 1 2\nMurch....\u201ci 3 2 1\nApri1....... |l7 16 7\nMay....... 29 5 2 18 1 3\nJune...... 40 1 i b\nJu1y........| 61 8 3 11 2\nAugust.....| 77\nSeptember 60 43 2 3 1\nOctober 120 27 19 18 3 1\nNovember..| 70 11 6 16 1 2 3\nDecember..| monls oW el ggy Sl\nTotal 1918 |3B 167 |B6| 33 9| 23 8\u00a7 4 [T 15\n1919\nJanuary.... 17 2 4 1\nFebruary. 3 2\nMarch...... 2 b 3\nApri1....... 8\nMay........ 1 1| 2 3 2\nJune....... 106 10 1 3\nJu1y........ 30 18 1 3\nAugust.....| 29 4 4\nSeptember 114 19 6 4 11\nOctober 81 18 14 118 1 13\nNovember. 100 28 11 26 6 1 4\nDecember 28 4 15 |.-5n85 6 1\nTotal 1919 352 206 106 163 9| |l2 |4% T 8\n1920\nJanuary.... 7 2 6 11 2 8 1\nFebruary. b 11 1 6 7 2\nMarch...... 3 3 3 17 8\nApri1....... 2 12 1\nMay........| 10 3 13 2 10\nJune....... 1 10 H 1 4 3\nJuly: Skl 13 18 6 2\nAugust. 1 8 1 2 10 6\nSeptember 56 37 34 16 1 2 3 6\nOctober 131 25 132 1 4 3 5\nNovember..| 64 36 10 b1 3 3 2 3\nDecember..| 3|25| 8| 1 5 9'\nTotal 1920 279 103 122 (199 9 38 |61|67 |@i\nYELLOW JACKET\n[Received to late for last week.\nMr. and Mrs. George Schaaf spent\nNew Year\u2019s day with their son, Fred\nand family, at their home near Little\nGrove.\nMrs. George Reese and little daugh\nter, Virginia May, left for Colorado\nSprings, Tuesday, to spend the rest of\nthe winter.\nMr. Reese was a Yellow Jacket\n'visitor a few days during the holidays.\nHe has been employed at Colorado\nSprings for the past few months, We\nwill miss this pleasant little family\nand will be glad to welcome their re\nturn in the spring.\nMiss Kathryn Willis returned to her\nschool at Trail\u2019s End (German school)\nafter a week\u2019s visit with the home\nfolks for Christmas.\nMiss Florence Dillon spent Christmas\nwith her sister, Mrs. Ed Wmbourn,\nand New Years with friends in Mancos\non her return to her school at Animas\nCity.\nHarry Rutherford came over from,\nDurango last Thursday and spent the\nweek end with relatives in Lewis,\nMrs. Billie Matthew of Cortez, spent\na few days last week with her son, Ed\nWinbourn.\nMiss Gailen Longenbaugh was a\nguest of her uncle, Ralph Dillon, and\nher aunt, Kitty Winbourn, during the\nholidays.\nHerb Croswaitt and family moved\ninto the new house at Lewis last week\nand the children have entered school.\nThe Four-Corners school is continued\nwith a good attendance, Miss Muriel\nDavig as teacher. Marian Willis, who\nhas been attending at Lewis has en\nrolled at Four Corners.\nHave you noticed the improvement\nin the Yellow Jacket store? Its flour\nspace is more than half again its\nformer size,\nSome of our farmers are taking ad\nvantage of these clear cold days to\nfinish hauding in theijr corn crop.\nSome people send off hundreds of\nmiles to buy articles at mail-order\nhouses, and then they are mad because\nlocal stores do not carry missing parts\nwhen the thing breaks down.\nSl S T\nMillions of People who object to food\nprices will never blister their own\nhands on hoe handle,\nSuch a relief! 1921 looks just like\nany other year.\nARMENIAN GIRL\nPLEADS FOR SISTERS\nTragic Tale of Harem Victims'\nSufferings.\nMore than ten thousand Armenian\ngiris have been rescued from Turklsh\nharems through the help and gener\nosity of America. This Is the state\nment given out by the Near East Re\nllef, which is making the saving of\nthese tragic victims of Turkish cruelty\none of the most important features of\nits work.\nThat it s a work which In itself\nJustifies the millions that America has\nspent In this stricken land is testified\nto by little Miss El'za Doduriap,\ntwenty-year-old Armenian girl recent\nly arrived In this country. Miss Dodu\nrlan, through the Intervention of Amer\nican missionaries, was herself soared\nELIZA DODURIAN.\nthe sufferings of exile and the horrors\nof slavery; but she knows all too well\nthe terrible fate of her sisters and\ntriends. It is for them\u2014the soft-eyed\nlittle girls of fifteen and sixteen whom\nlast she saw belng torn from thelr\nmothers' arms and carried off on the\nsaddle bows of the Turkish soldiers\u2014\nthat she makes her plea.\nWhat their lives have been since\nthen may be guessed by a look Into the\nfaces of any of the ten thousand who\nhave passed through the Rescue Homes\nof the Near Kast Relief. Thelr heads\nbowed In shame, they creep Into the\nAmerican rellef stations, trying vainly\nto hide the tattoo marks which pro\nclaim to the world their story.\nThousands of these girls have beed\nbrought back to life and hope through\nthe work of the Near East Rellef. It\n18 to rescue the one hundred theusand\nmere still held captive that the Neaf\nEast Rellef {s making its appeal this\nyear, i","height":"20104","width":"13912"}}
